mindmap
  root((AI Development Life Cycle))
    Ideation and Problem Framing
      - Clarify measurable business outcomes
      - Bridge executive intent with data strategy
      - Set legal, privacy, and ethical boundaries
      - Define ownership from the outset
    Data Preparation and Governance
      - Discovery, auditing, cleaning, labeling
      - Resolve quality issues and systemic bias
      - Ensure compliance and access controls
      - Design repeatable, scalable pipelines
    Model Development and Experimentation
      - Governed sandbox for exploration
      - Version tracking and reproducibility
      - Align models to operational requirements
      - Define production-readiness criteria
    Validation and Evaluation
      - Fairness across demographics and contexts
      - Robustness and edge case testing
      - Business stakeholder engagement
      - Cross-functional go/no-go governance
    Deployment and Integration
      - Automated CI/CD pipelines
      - Downstream system integration
      - Rollback mechanisms and compliance logging
      - Staged rollout and version tracking
    Monitoring and Observability
      - Active performance and drift detection
      - Business outcome tracking
      - Compliance signal monitoring
      - Clear ownership and escalation paths
    Feedback, Retraining, and Retirement
      - Designed feedback loops
      - Governed retraining triggers and policies
      - Planned model end-of-life
      - Archive, sunset, and document